# open-darf — Peer Validator (Phase 7Y)


Windows-first onboarding with **cancel-safe heartbeats**. Linux/WSL works too.

## Quickstart (Linux/WSL)
~~~bash
bash ./scripts/run.sh
bash ./scripts/validator_acceptance.sh
~~~

## Quickstart (Windows PowerShell)
~~~powershell
powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\run.ps1
powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\validate.ps1
~~~

### What runs
- `compose.sanitized.yml` → **MinIO** (API 9000 / Console 9001) and **Postgres**
- **Qdrant** (HTTP only) + **Neo4j** run as bare containers
- Heartbeats print every ~2s; **Ctrl-C** cancels instantly
- Evidence/receipts are written under `results/`

### Troubleshooting (ports busy)
~~~bash
bash ./scripts/kill_switch.sh
bash ./scripts/run.sh    # will re-pick free ports for Qdrant; MinIO can be remapped via override
~~~

